description: The date when the event was logged (YYYYMMDD format in the registered timezone of your app).
The time (in microseconds, UTC) when the event was logged on the client.
The name of the event.

The event_params RECORD can store campaign-level and contextual event parameters as well as any user-defined event parameters. The event_params RECORD is repeated for each key that is associated with an event. The set of parameters stored in the event_params RECORD is unique to each implementation. To see the complete list of event parameters for your implementation, query the event parameter list.
The name of the event parameter.
A record containing the event parameter's value.
If the event parameter is represented by a string, such as a URL or campaign name, it is populated in this field.
If the event parameter is represented by an integer, it is populated in this field.
If the event parameter is represented by a floating point value, it is populated in this field. This field is not currently in use.
If the event parameter is represented by a double value, it is populated in this field.
The time (in microseconds, UTC) when the event was previously logged on the client.
The currency-converted value (in USD) of the event's "value" parameter.
The sequential ID of the bundle in which these events were uploaded.
Timestamp offset between collection time and upload time in micros.
The unique ID assigned to a user.
The pseudonymous id (e.g., app instance ID) for the user.
The privacy_info fields contain information based on the consent status of a user when consent mode is enabled.
Whether Analytics storage is enabled for the user. Possible values: Yes, No, Unset
Whether ad targeting is enabled for a user. Possible values: Yes, No, Unset
Whether a web user has denied Analytics storage and the developer has enabled measurement without cookies based on transient tokens in server data. Possible values: Yes, No, Unset
The user_properties RECORD contains any user properties that you have set. It is repeated for each key that is associated with a user.
The name of the user property.
A record for the user property value.
The string value of the user property.
The integer value of the user property.
This field is currently unused.
The double value of the user property.
The time (in microseconds) at which the user property was last set.
The time (in microseconds) at which the user first opened the app or visited the site.
The user_ltv RECORD contains Lifetime Value information about the user. This RECORD is not populated in intraday tables.
The Lifetime Value (revenue) of the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.
The Lifetime Value (currency) of the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.
The device RECORD contains information about the device from which the event originated.
The device category (mobile, tablet, desktop).
The device brand name.
The device model name.
The device marketing name.
The device model information retrieved directly from the operating system.
The operating system of the device.
The OS version.
IDFV (present only if IDFA is not collected).
Advertising ID/IDFA.
The OS language.
The device's Limit Ad Tracking setting. On iOS14+, returns false if the IDFA is non-zero.
The offset from GMT in seconds.
The browser in which the user viewed content.
The version of the browser in which the user viewed content.
The geo RECORD contains information about the geographic location where the event was initiated.
The continent from which events were reported, based on IP address.
The subcontinent from which events were reported, based on IP address.
The country from which events were reported, based on IP address.
The region from which events were reported, based on IP address.
The city from which events were reported, based on IP address.
The metro from which events were reported, based on IP address.
The app_info RECORD contains information about the app in which the event was initiated.
The package name or bundle ID of the app.
The app's versionName (Android) or short bundle version.
The Firebase App ID associated with the app
The store that installed the app.

The traffic_source RECORD contains information about the traffic source that first acquired the user. This record is not populated in intraday tables. Note: The traffic_source values do not change if the user interacts with subsequent campaigns after installation.
Name of the medium (paid search, organic search, email, etc.) that first acquired the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.
Name of the marketing campaign that first acquired the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.
Name of the network that first acquired the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.
The numeric ID of the data stream from which the event originated.
The data stream platform (Web, IOS or Android) from which the event originated.
The hostname associated with the logged event.
This ecommerce RECORD contains information about any ecommerce events that have been setup on a website or app.
Total number of items in this event, which is the sum of items.quantity.
Purchase revenue of this event, represented in USD with standard unit. Populated for purchase event only.
Purchase revenue of this event, represented in local currency with standard unit. Populated for purchase event only.
The amount of refund in this event, represented in USD with standard unit. Populated for refund event only.
The amount of refund in this event, represented in local currency with standard unit. Populated for refund event only.
The shipping cost in this event, represented in USD with standard unit.
The shipping cost in this event, represented in local currency.
The tax value in this event, represented in USD with standard unit.
The tax value in this event, represented in local currency with standard unit.
The number of unique items in this event, based on item_id, item_name, and item_brand.
The transaction ID of the ecommerce transaction.
The items RECORD contains information about items included in an event. It is repeated for each item.
The ID of the item.
The name of the item.
The brand of the item.
The variant of the item.
The category of the item.
The sub category of the item.
The sub category of the item.
The sub category of the item.
The sub category of the item.
The price of the item, in USD with standard unit.
The price of the item in local currency.
The quantity of the item. Quantity set to 1 if not specified.
The revenue of this item, calculated as price_in_usd * quantity. It is populated for purchase events only, in USD with standard unit.
The revenue of this item, calculated as price * quantity. It is populated for purchase events only, in local currency with standard unit.
The refund value of this item, calculated as price_in_usd * quantity. It is populated for refund events only, in USD with standard unit.
The refund value of this item, calculated as price * quantity. It is populated for refund events only, in local currency with standard unit.
Coupon code applied to this item.
A product affiliation to designate a supplying company or brick and mortar store location.
The location associated with the item.
The ID of the list in which the item was presented to the user.
The name of the list in which the item was presented to the user.
The position of the item in a list.
The ID of a product promotion.
The name of a product promotion.
The name of a creative used in a promotional spot.
The name of a creative slot.
